The paper deals with the problem of content caching and transmission in a wireless network, which is a typical problem in the field of networked systems and communication (cs.NI). The paper also involves the use of deep learning algorithms to optimize the content caching and transmission, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.MM) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the impact of various network factors on content caching and transmission, which is related to information theory (cs.IT) and control systems (cs.SY).
